      "writtenOn": "2015-08-04T23:55:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We really want to check that the generated binaries target our deployment target. If the number is smaller, it\u0027s probably a symptom that there is something wrong with the toolchain being used.\n\nBesides, this will not work in Unix shells, where \u003e is used for redirections, you\u0027re looking for -gt, a.k.a \"greater than\". Besides, -gt will make a lexicographical compare, so \"10.10\" will be smaller than \"10.8\" with it.",
      "parentUuid": "eadf9421_1edc4204",
      "revId": "8ba5675cf5f812a88c622626b59939ca8ecf41b7",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
